<TITLE> Ex-BNP ministers, MP sued for backing militancy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)Former BNP-led coalition government ministers Aminul Haq and Ruhul Kuddus Talukdar Dulu, ex-MP Nadim Mostofa and 6 others were sued Wednesday on charges of backing militancy and beating up a man for extortion in Rajshahi. Haq and Mostofa have been on the run since the state of emergency was declared in Jan. 2007. UP member Abed Ali of Mirzapur under Bagmara Upazila filed the case with the court of Rajshahi judicial magistrate-3 Asaf-ud-Dowla. The court, taking the case into cognisance, ordered the officer in charge of Bagmara Police Station to take legal steps after investigation. The case in brief is that banned Jamatul Mujahideen Bangladesh cadres besieged and broke into the complainant's house at around 9pm on Apr 13, 2006. They took him out and beat him up for extortion at their local torture camp. The former ministers and MP, Shish Mohammad, general secretary of Rajshahi city unit of BNP, Rafiqul Islam, chairman of Bihali Union Parisad, Beshratullah, chairman of Bashupara Union Parisad, professor Lutfar Rahman and Abdus Sattar directed the JMB cadres, he alleged. Ali told reporters that he could not file a case earlier as he was scared of reprisal. Babul Hossain Bablu, lawyer for the plaintiff, said 17 people have been made witnesses to the case. bdn
